      About this item

      • Touch & Voice-Assistant Control Stay connected and hands-free with Tulbeys' GS06 smart glasses with bluetooth 5.3 and voice assistant to listen to music, make calls, and control your media without lifting a finger.
      • Protective & Color-changing Lenses Protect your eyes with fast-reacting Photochromic lenses that change color in 3 seconds, anti blue light protection, and polarized sunglasses that balance style and functionality with smart Bluetooth technology.
      • Open Ear Smart Glasses Experience an open-ear sound experience with automatic noise reduction for clear and uninterrupted audio with Polarizing lenses with UV400 protection perfect for fishing, hiking, riding, driving, and outdoor activities.
      • Long Battery Life Enjoy fast charging with magnetic charging ports and a 4-6 hours of use time in PC frame glasses with dual speakers and a touch control area with remote camera function for convenience.
      • Professional Design Available in unisex design, the GS06 smart glasses offer voice control, IPX5 waterproofing, and a sleek athletic look that combines technology and nature for men and women on-the-go.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        I saw all these great reviews and thought I'd give these a try since they're not super expensive anyway. They came in this morning and I immediately opened them and began to charge them. I noticed once I connect the magnetic part to the phone, it stays lit for like 5 seconds and then the light goes off. I assumed that meant they weren't staying connected somehow, so I moved them several different positions and it immediately stops charging no matter how I set it. I'm gonna give it some more time, but if this persists, I'm gonna have to return them.
        I did try them out for a few minutes and the connection was easy, sound quality was good, and the glasses are really cute. I just can't get over the fact I've not been able to keep them continuously charging for more than a few seconds at a time. I was excited, too.

        Update*
        I got them to charge up using a different outlet overnight, but the battery life of them wasn't even as long as it was when I first got them and couldn't charge them. I need to do a little more research on these and may possibly need to send them back for a different pair in case these are defective. I was really excited about these, too. I'll give it a couple more days and see how I feel...
